WEBVTT

00:01.752 --> 00:03.333
MOHINDER:
Previously on Heroes.

00:03.504 --> 00:05.085
(SCREAMING)

00:05.173 --> 00:06.663
ARTHUR:
/ must wipe your memory.

00:06.799 --> 00:08.300
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:08.426 --> 00:09.506
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:09.594 --> 00:10.834
9th Wonders!

00:10.928 --> 00:13.135
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:14.473 --> 00:16.009
Can we leave
Matt out of this?

00:16.100 --> 00:19.968
If you're unhappy, I can
always arrange for you
to return to your former life.

00:20.104 --> 00:22.641
DAPHNE: Just tell me what
I’m supposed to do.
ARTHUR: Stay with Parkman.

00:22.773 --> 00:24.479
I came here looking for you,
and what did I find?

00:24.609 --> 00:27.271
You're waiting for me.
I mean, that's gotta
mean something, right?

00:27.945 --> 00:29.355
GABRIEL: You saved
my life once, Elle.

00:29.447 --> 00:30.778
Don't you see?
I owe you.

00:30.865 --> 00:32.025
I forgive you.

00:32.116 --> 00:33.947
Now you need
to forgive yourself.

00:34.994 --> 00:39.158
Arthur's probably figured out
by now that there's
a third piece of the formula.

00:39.248 --> 00:40.328
It's a catalyst.

00:40.416 --> 00:42.702
Hidden away
in the blood
of a human host.

00:42.793 --> 00:43.953
I think
I'm the catalyst.

00:45.254 --> 00:47.791
| see we share
a fascination.

00:47.882 --> 00:49.713
It seems
most of the powers
l've documented

00:49.800 --> 00:52.291
took place during the last
total annular eclipse.

00:53.930 --> 00:55.010
It's coming.

01:00.603 --> 01:04.642
MOHINDER:
There’s a moment in every war
where everything changes.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.898
A moment when the road bends.

01:08.736 --> 01:14.527
Alliances and battle lines
shift, and the rules of
engagement are rewritten.

01:15.660 --> 01:18.493
Moments like these
can change the nature
of the battle,

01:19.664 --> 01:22.497
and turn the tide
for either side.

01:23.125 --> 01:26.333
So we do what we can
to understand them.

01:29.131 --> 01:33.124
To be ready for change,
we steady our hearts,

01:33.219 --> 01:39.840
curb our fears,
muster our forces, and
look for signs in the stars.

01:48.025 --> 01:49.640
At these moments,

01:49.735 --> 01:53.944
these game changes
remain a mystery.

01:54.031 --> 01:58.274
Destiny’s invisible hand
moving pieces on a chessboard.

01:59.787 --> 02:04.030
No matter how much
we prepare for them,
how much we resist the change,

02:04.125 --> 02:09.165
anticipate the moment,
fight the inevitable outcome,

02:09.255 --> 02:15.342
in the end,
we’re never truly
ready when it strikes.

02:19.223 --> 02:20.963
You're getting
pretty good at that.

02:23.394 --> 02:24.634
You'll get there,
don't sweat it.

02:24.729 --> 02:27.345
Well, I need to
get there now.
l have to prove myself.

02:30.443 --> 02:31.728
To who?

02:32.945 --> 02:35.482
He's nobody,
I'm not sure
you'd understand.

02:39.410 --> 02:41.901
Okay.
Then let's go again.

02:43.372 --> 02:46.990
Gabriel, I need you
to do something.

02:47.084 --> 02:50.042
Find Claire Bennet.
Bring her back to me.

02:50.671 --> 02:53.504
You think you can do that?
Yes, sir,
of course, I can.

02:56.427 --> 02:58.588
I'm going, too.
What?

02:59.847 --> 03:02.759
Well, they're not
gonna make it easy
for you, getting Claire.

03:02.850 --> 03:07.435
You need help,
and l was raised to
be a Company girl.

03:07.521 --> 03:10.137
Hey, wait,
I thought you'd left
all that behind you.

03:10.608 --> 03:13.566
Yeah, well,
it's all I know.

03:14.236 --> 03:15.772
You need help.

03:16.614 --> 03:17.899
Let me help you.

03:19.033 --> 03:20.569
You okay with this,
Dad?

03:22.787 --> 03:25.449
I think the two
of you together,

03:27.375 --> 03:28.785
it's a good pairing.

03:30.252 --> 03:31.958
Let's go get
the cheerleader.

03:35.466 --> 03:37.457
(SIGHING)
Why is it always me?

03:37.551 --> 03:40.634
You're the catalyst,
Arthur's formula doesn't
work without you.

03:40.763 --> 03:43.971
l have a plan,
but we all have to work
together to stop him.

03:44.100 --> 03:45.556
Okay,
so where's everyone else?

03:45.643 --> 03:49.886
Nathan is going to find
the Haitian, Matt Parkman
will get Hiro Nakamura,

03:49.980 --> 03:53.222
and you, Claire,
have the most
important part to play.

03:53.317 --> 03:54.727
Great!
What's my assignment?

03:54.819 --> 03:57.902
Your assignment
is to keep
from getting caught.

03:57.988 --> 03:59.569
Just stay out
of harm's way.

03:59.657 --> 04:02.774
But I can fight.
I can do more,
I can be more.

04:02.868 --> 04:05.735
Only place you're going
to be is underground,
off the grid.

04:05.830 --> 04:09.789
No. No way.
lam clone hiding.

04:09.875 --> 04:11.831
We all have
to make sacrifices.

04:15.464 --> 04:17.420
What are you gonna do,
lock me up?

04:17.508 --> 04:20.545
Don't think it hasn't
crossed my mind, but no.

04:21.512 --> 04:23.002
l have another plan.

04:36.861 --> 04:38.317
Hi, Claire-bear.

04:43.033 --> 04:44.819
It's too dangerous
for you to
go there alone.

04:44.910 --> 04:47.287
I'm just going down
there to get the Haitian,
and I'm coming right back.

04:47.371 --> 04:49.111
The Haitian is there
to hunt down
a Level 5 escapee,

04:49.206 --> 04:52.118
this guy,
Baron Samedi, look.

04:52.209 --> 04:55.326
Baron?
No, it's an alias.
Voodoo God of Death.

04:55.421 --> 04:58.504
This guy's into some
bad stuff, drug trafficking,
kidnapping, slavery.

04:58.591 --> 05:00.297
I'm telling you, Nathan,
you're going
to need some help.

05:00.384 --> 05:03.592
Pete, I'm not
going down there
to save the country.

05:03.679 --> 05:05.215
Okay, just...

05:06.390 --> 05:08.722
You don't understand.
Then help me out.

05:10.728 --> 05:13.561
When I found my abilities,
I knew who
I was supposed to be.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.558
Okay? But now...
Pete.

05:15.649 --> 05:20.484
Just because you don't have
your abilities, it doesn't
mean you don't have a purpose.

05:20.571 --> 05:22.562
It will if you don't
take me with you.

05:24.450 --> 05:25.781
Nathan...

05:30.581 --> 05:31.661
All right.

05:33.083 --> 05:34.243
Come on.

05:55.940 --> 05:57.146
(INHALES SHARPLY)

06:07.952 --> 06:09.863
I need the catalyst.
You said you would
have it by now.

06:09.954 --> 06:11.319
You said you were
going to cure me!

06:11.455 --> 06:15.698
I've got people on it,
but all our plans
might be for nothing.

06:15.793 --> 06:17.704
What are you talking about?

06:17.795 --> 06:21.208
I drew that.
It's going to happen. Today.

06:23.217 --> 06:25.833
This is Claire Bennet.
She can't die,
it's impossible.

06:25.928 --> 06:29.841
That's my point.
It can't happen,
but it's going to.

06:29.932 --> 06:33.891
You're the scientist.
You tell me how.

06:35.854 --> 06:37.139
(SIGHING)

06:37.231 --> 06:39.313
There's an eclipse today.
Yes.

06:39.400 --> 06:42.142
When I first noted
abilities manifesting,
there was an eclipse.

06:42.278 --> 06:44.234
A global event.
You said it was
a coincidence.

06:44.363 --> 06:46.103
Well, I thought
it was, but...
But what?

06:46.198 --> 06:49.190
What does it mean?
Look, I don't know!

06:49.285 --> 06:53.745
But I do know if Claire
Bennet dies, then
the catalyst dies with her.

06:54.373 --> 06:56.659
And there's no hope
for me being cured.

06:59.503 --> 07:01.289
That explains this.

07:02.506 --> 07:04.292
I'm going to die.

07:05.467 --> 07:09.585
Everything's going
to change today.
Everything.

07:28.324 --> 07:31.737
I don't understand
what Hiro Nakamura has
to do with any of this.

07:31.827 --> 07:34.284
Angela made
our orders very clear.

07:34.371 --> 07:36.032
Yeah, the guy's a spaz.

07:36.123 --> 07:38.079
No, he's a time-traveler.

07:38.167 --> 07:41.204
lfArthur Petrelli has us
on the ropes, the man
is a walking do-over.

07:41.295 --> 07:44.207
I know I have Hiro's number
in his dad's homicide file.

07:44.298 --> 07:46.254
Are you nervous
about something?

07:47.509 --> 07:48.794
Arthur Petrelli scares me.

07:48.886 --> 07:50.296
Oh, you don't have
to be scared about him.

07:50.387 --> 07:54.551
Of course I do.
He can take away abilities,
and l betrayed him.

07:54.642 --> 07:57.224
l betrayed you.
No, no, you didn't.

07:57.311 --> 07:59.017
I'm a betrayer.
What?

07:59.146 --> 08:00.761
And a liar,
and a thief, and...
No.

08:00.856 --> 08:03.973
And I'm selfish. You know,
honestly, I don't understand
why you even keep me around.

08:04.068 --> 08:05.604
Because you're one
of the good guys now.

08:05.694 --> 08:06.934
So you trust me?
Yes.

08:07.029 --> 08:08.269
Completely?

08:09.156 --> 08:12.865
Yes, I trust you completely.
I know you, Daphne.

08:12.951 --> 08:15.283
Yeah, well, no.
You say that, but you
don't know me. Not really.

08:15.371 --> 08:16.827
We had a life together.

08:18.082 --> 08:19.367
It was a spirit walk.

08:19.458 --> 08:21.449
It wasn't real.

08:21.543 --> 08:24.785
(SIGHS) Arthur killed
your father, he could
kill us all, or worse. I...

08:24.880 --> 08:27.917
I'm not gonna let
anything happen to you.
I promise.

08:28.008 --> 08:31.341
Please, just help me
find Hiro. Come on.

08:31.428 --> 08:35.137
How are we gonna do
that exactly? The guy's
a freaking teleporter.

08:35.224 --> 08:37.055
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

08:40.938 --> 08:42.724
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

08:43.941 --> 08:47.399
Hey, I need your help.
You have to fix Hiro.
Look.

08:49.238 --> 08:50.569
What does it say?

08:50.656 --> 08:53.864
It says you have to
fix Hiro. Arthur Petrelli
erased his memory.

08:53.951 --> 08:55.987
Hiro now thinks
he's 10 years old.

08:56.662 --> 08:58.618
(HIRO EXCLAIMING)

08:58.706 --> 09:00.571
Oh, it's back there.

09:04.920 --> 09:06.035
(DOOR SLAMS)

09:06.130 --> 09:07.461
We're all gonna die.

09:17.558 --> 09:19.890
This is Stephen
Canfield's house.

09:19.977 --> 09:23.344
You'll be safe here.
Out of harm's way.

09:25.149 --> 09:28.186
Last time we were here,
we almost got sucked
into a black hole.

09:28.277 --> 09:29.892
What makes it
so safe now?

09:29.987 --> 09:32.774
Simple setup.
Controllable.

09:33.615 --> 09:36.106
I know how you like
to control things.

09:37.995 --> 09:40.782
Okay, I'll bite.
What does that mean?

09:40.873 --> 09:44.331
It means you'll do
whatever it takes to keep
the catalyst safe, right?

09:44.418 --> 09:49.162
Hey, lwanna keep
you safe, Claire. You.

09:49.965 --> 09:51.580
Not some catalyst.

09:52.551 --> 09:54.007
Do you understand?

09:54.094 --> 09:55.504
Yeah, I understand.

10:02.019 --> 10:04.180
(H/RO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

10:13.155 --> 10:15.942
Aren't you dead?
Yeah. You'd like that.

10:16.033 --> 10:17.694
What's your game, nemesis?

10:17.785 --> 10:20.868
I'm not a nemesis anymore.
I'm a good guy now.

10:20.954 --> 10:24.117
I can't help him,
I can't understand him.

10:24.208 --> 10:27.200
Well, Arthur really
did a number on Hiro.
He really thinks he's 10.

10:27.294 --> 10:28.659
So, get inside
his head and fix him.

10:28.754 --> 10:31.040
I don't think I can.
He's thinking in Japanese.

10:31.173 --> 10:33.459
But the comic book
says that you...
I don't know
what to tell you.

10:33.550 --> 10:34.665
This is way beyond me.

10:34.760 --> 10:37.547
Hiro is our reset button.
Our walking do-over, remember?

10:37.638 --> 10:42.223
I know, but he still can
time travel, he can teleport,
and he's still very powerful.

10:43.477 --> 10:44.967
(ANDO SIGHS)

10:49.733 --> 10:52.566
I can't...
I can't do this, I'm sorry,
I gotta get out of here.

10:52.653 --> 10:56.111
What? What are you
talking about? Daphne.

10:56.198 --> 10:57.938
You paused.
What?

10:59.743 --> 11:02.450
When I asked you
if you trusted me,
you paused.

11:02.538 --> 11:03.823
No. No, I didn't.

11:03.914 --> 11:05.404
I'm a speedster.

11:05.499 --> 11:09.083
Fractions of seconds
feel like hours to me,
and you paused.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.581
You don't know me,
and you don't know
what I've been through.

11:11.672 --> 11:14.038
What is that
supposed to mean?
Daphne, come on.

11:15.926 --> 11:17.962
Matt?
Lawrence, Kansas?

11:18.095 --> 11:20.131
Stop reading my mind.
What's in Kansas?
Come on.

11:20.222 --> 11:22.087
Just back off!
Your home.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.763
Leave me alone!

11:27.938 --> 11:30.224
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

11:34.194 --> 11:36.150
Yes, sir,
it'll all be
taken care of.

11:40.534 --> 11:42.741
Who was on the phone?
Arthur.

11:42.828 --> 11:45.695
Just updating him on
our status. He thinks
Claire is with her father.

11:45.789 --> 11:46.824
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)

11:46.915 --> 11:48.621
Glasses himself.

11:48.709 --> 11:51.451
He's scary,
he's not going to
make this any easier.

11:51.545 --> 11:53.251
Actually, he is.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.249
I don't want him
to get inside my head
so he could kill me,

11:55.340 --> 11:57.251
but it'd work both ways.

11:57.342 --> 11:59.128
I know how he thinks.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.459
I know where
he'll hide her.

12:00.554 --> 12:02.465
I'm worried about you.

12:02.556 --> 12:06.140
All these "Yes, sirs"
and checking in
like a good little boy.

12:07.895 --> 12:09.601
Just trying to
be responsible.

12:10.856 --> 12:12.892
Oh, sure.
Responsible.

12:15.485 --> 12:17.737
Where is this damn
rental car guy?

12:17.821 --> 12:19.607
Probably
calling the police

12:19.698 --> 12:23.236
because I told him
you were a serial killer
and that you kidnapped me.

12:25.871 --> 12:27.486
You must be joking.
Why the hell
would you do that?

12:27.581 --> 12:29.867
Because I'm trying
to help you.

12:29.958 --> 12:33.075
Because it was wrong
of the Company
to hide our abilities.

12:33.170 --> 12:35.661
Because we can do
whatever we want.

12:35.756 --> 12:39.340
We can take
whatever we want.
Trust me.

12:39.426 --> 12:41.337
Come on. We're going.

12:41.428 --> 12:42.508
MAN: You're not
going anywhere!

12:42.596 --> 12:43.711
(GASPS) Oh, God.

12:43.805 --> 12:45.796
Oh, help, please help.
Please.

12:45.891 --> 12:47.722
Let go of the girl.

12:50.854 --> 12:54.346
Thank you.
Oh, God, thank you.
Oh, my God, thank you.

12:55.359 --> 12:58.351
Sir, please put down the gun.
You really don't understand
what's happening here.

12:58.445 --> 13:01.653
She filled me in pretty good.
You serial-killing scum
of the earth.

13:01.740 --> 13:04.857
They're all trying
to make you into something.

13:04.952 --> 13:10.743
A boy scout, a monster.
Who's it gonna be, huh?
Who are you really?

13:10.832 --> 13:11.912
Shut up.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.912
I should kill you right now,
say it was self-defense.

13:15.003 --> 13:17.494
I'll be famous,
a bona fide hero.

13:18.382 --> 13:19.371
(GROANS)

13:25.931 --> 13:27.592
I hate heroes.

13:36.900 --> 13:41.940
What does this eclipse mean,
and how could it
possibly affect us?

13:42.030 --> 13:43.531
(COUGHING)

13:44.950 --> 13:48.784
The moon controls
the ocean's waves, the sun,
our internal timing,

13:48.870 --> 13:52.328
but something is
happening to me.

13:53.500 --> 13:54.740
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

13:54.835 --> 13:57.076
l'm changing,
I can feel it.

14:00.716 --> 14:02.456
And I can't control it.

14:04.011 --> 14:05.626
(COUGHING)

14:24.364 --> 14:25.353
(SIGHING)

14:30.162 --> 14:31.197
What's this for?

14:31.288 --> 14:32.448
Hit me with it.

14:33.331 --> 14:36.243
You wanted me to train you?
Let's do it, right here,
right now.

14:37.169 --> 14:41.333
This is how you get over
your guilt? Because I've
been just fine without you.

14:41.423 --> 14:42.708
Have you?

14:42.799 --> 14:44.209
(SCOFFS)

14:44.718 --> 14:45.878
I caught the puppet guy.

14:45.969 --> 14:47.550
Yeah. You got lucky.

14:47.637 --> 14:50.845
And you almost got your
mother killed. These are
serious, dangerous criminals.

14:50.932 --> 14:52.388
I know.
You're not acting like it.

14:52.476 --> 14:54.933
What am I acting like?
Like a girl
who can't get hurt.

14:55.020 --> 14:56.760
Stupid and careless.

14:56.855 --> 14:59.562
What do you know?
You're the one
who left, remember?

14:59.649 --> 15:02.561
My absence does not
give you license
to act like a brat.

15:02.652 --> 15:05.610
l have been trying
to do something
good with my ability.

15:05.697 --> 15:07.278
And I'm trying
to keep you safe.

15:07.365 --> 15:08.741
I don't need your help!

15:08.825 --> 15:10.281
Then hit me.

15:10.911 --> 15:12.447
I said hit me.

15:14.664 --> 15:16.791
(GRUNTING)

15:18.835 --> 15:21.212
The good news is
you've certainly
got the strength.

15:21.296 --> 15:24.003
The bad news is
you're clumsy,
slow and obvious.

15:24.132 --> 15:27.875
Thanks.
This time,
get your body weight into it.

15:27.969 --> 15:31.632
That way all the power will
be on the end of the board.
Okay? Let's go again.

15:33.391 --> 15:34.927
What is this,
Taekwon-Do?

15:35.018 --> 15:37.430
No, it's baseball.

15:38.480 --> 15:40.061
Let's go again.

15:41.316 --> 15:44.479
lt's Tracy.
Nathan's veering off plan.

15:45.153 --> 15:47.109
He's going to find
this Haitian guy.

15:47.197 --> 15:49.779
ARTHUR: That’s smart,
using the Haitian against me.

15:50.450 --> 15:51.906
We can't have that.

15:51.993 --> 15:53.699
You're not gonna hurt him?

15:53.787 --> 15:57.371
I'm learning today
there are some things
out of my control.

15:57.457 --> 15:59.243
What is that
supposed to mean?

15:59.334 --> 16:02.371
It’s time for Nathan
to see the world
for what it really is.

16:04.422 --> 16:06.037
Look, I agreed
to help you

16:06.133 --> 16:08.920
because you said
that we could get Nathan
into the White House.

16:09.010 --> 16:10.216
You need him, Arthur.

16:10.303 --> 16:11.679
So do you.

16:12.722 --> 16:16.135
I need you to go
to Parris Island, use those
connections you've got.

16:16.226 --> 16:17.636
I don't take
orders from you.

16:17.727 --> 16:21.845
If you want your way
into the Oval Office,
you'll do exactly as I say.

16:25.318 --> 16:26.933
Parris Island.

16:30.407 --> 16:32.193
The Marine
training facility?

16:32.284 --> 16:34.525
Every war needs an army.

16:37.831 --> 16:39.367
Washington.

16:40.750 --> 16:41.830
(SIGHS)

16:41.918 --> 16:44.125
I guess there's
no rest
for the wicked.

16:44.212 --> 16:45.793
Obviously not.

16:51.052 --> 16:52.758
I need Hiro
to help me
find Daphne.

16:52.846 --> 16:54.336
But she stole
the formula,
she's a villain.

16:54.431 --> 16:56.046
No, she's not.
She's just scared.

16:56.141 --> 16:57.221
Of what?
I don't know.

16:57.309 --> 16:59.174
I don't know,
but I gotta find out.

16:59.269 --> 17:02.352
(SIGHS) Oh, God,
I told her
that I doubted her.

17:02.856 --> 17:04.562
l practically
packed her bags for her.

17:04.649 --> 17:06.810
Look,
we need to help Hiro.

17:06.902 --> 17:08.483
Get him back to normal,
stop Arthur Petrelli...

17:08.570 --> 17:09.605
But it'll only
take a minute.

17:09.696 --> 17:12.654
All he has to do is
teleport me to Lawrence,
Kansas, I grab Daphne, and...

17:12.741 --> 17:14.197
Lawrence, Kansas?

17:15.785 --> 17:17.400
Lawrence, Kansas.

17:17.495 --> 17:19.827
Yes! That's us.
We're in a cornfield.

17:19.915 --> 17:21.530
She told me
that she grew up
on a corn farm.

17:21.625 --> 17:22.865
Corn farm.
Yeah.

17:22.959 --> 17:25.291
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

17:25.754 --> 17:26.834
Lawrence, Kansas.

17:26.922 --> 17:28.002
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

17:35.055 --> 17:38.343
Holy crap, it worked.
This is it,
this is Daphne's house.

17:39.684 --> 17:41.766
I can hear her thoughts,
she's in there.

17:43.647 --> 17:45.057
Holy crap!

17:52.697 --> 17:53.982
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

17:57.953 --> 17:59.068
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

19:24.122 --> 19:25.111
(GROANS)

19:41.848 --> 19:44.555
Pete. Pete.

19:44.642 --> 19:46.018
You all right?
Yeah.

19:46.102 --> 19:48.263
Yeah, I'm okay. You?

19:48.938 --> 19:50.064
I'm good.

19:50.148 --> 19:51.183
What happened?

19:51.274 --> 19:53.560
I don't know.
I was flying
and then I wasn't.

19:53.651 --> 19:55.266
l was falling really fast.

19:55.362 --> 19:56.818
And now?

19:56.905 --> 19:58.861
Nothing. I can't fly.

20:02.160 --> 20:04.276
Hey, wasn't there
an eclipse that
first day you flew?

20:04.371 --> 20:06.282
Yeah, so?

20:07.791 --> 20:09.782
So you don't find
that significant?

20:10.794 --> 20:12.876
The guy we're looking for,
the Haitian,
he takes powers away.

20:12.962 --> 20:17.296
Maybe he saw us coming.
I don't know. Maybe it's
this whole damn country.

20:18.635 --> 20:20.421
We gotta find him.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.384
Come on,
let's make tracks.
All right.

20:25.225 --> 20:27.011
Got a long walk
ahead of us.

20:34.067 --> 20:35.978
What the hell are these,
voodoo dolls?

20:36.069 --> 20:40.233
No, they're called pwen.
They're messengers.

20:41.157 --> 20:43.648
Prayers for salvation,
redemption.

20:44.869 --> 20:45.904
Let's go.

20:45.995 --> 20:48.782
Looking at the map,
the Haitian's village
is this way.

20:49.999 --> 20:52.251
I saw it from
two clicks up.

20:52.335 --> 20:53.541
We were falling.

20:53.628 --> 20:54.663
Yeah.

20:55.004 --> 20:56.164
It's still this way.

20:56.256 --> 20:58.292
Hey, are you...
Don't you want...

21:10.812 --> 21:12.348
(DOOR OPENING)

21:14.023 --> 21:16.765
Something I can
do for you?
Hi, yeah.

21:16.860 --> 21:19.818
I'm a friend of Daphne's,
can I talk to her
for a second?

21:19.904 --> 21:21.815
Daphne's not here.

21:21.906 --> 21:25.023
Daphne! I know
you're inside, come on.
ljust need a minute.

21:25.118 --> 21:26.699
DAPHNE: GO away, Matt.

21:29.539 --> 21:32.121
Like I said,
she's not home.

21:32.709 --> 21:36.372
Yeah. Why don't you
just let me inside?

21:37.714 --> 21:39.375
Are you threatening me?

21:43.094 --> 21:47.133
I said let me in.

21:49.934 --> 21:52.801
Why are you turning
your head sideways?

21:53.980 --> 21:55.936
What's your problem,
son?

22:01.446 --> 22:02.481
Psst.

22:02.572 --> 22:04.062
What happened?

22:06.659 --> 22:07.819
My powers are gone.

22:07.911 --> 22:09.242
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

22:11.414 --> 22:12.915
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

22:13.124 --> 22:15.331
His also.
What's going on?

22:25.762 --> 22:27.923
Are you gonna
tell me who that was?

22:29.182 --> 22:30.171
Nope.

22:30.266 --> 22:33.178
I'm not asking a lot
of questions here.

22:33.269 --> 22:34.850
And I appreciate that.

22:34.938 --> 22:37.429
But you've been
gone a long time.

22:38.983 --> 22:40.484
It's my home.

22:41.486 --> 22:43.101
Can't I just come home?

22:46.950 --> 22:48.941
Are you feeling okay?

22:51.371 --> 22:52.451
No.

22:57.585 --> 22:59.121
lt's happening again.

23:03.341 --> 23:06.208
Sweetheart, I'm sorry.

23:06.886 --> 23:08.092
Do you still have them?

23:08.179 --> 23:09.339
Yeah.

23:09.806 --> 23:12.218
Yeah,
I'll go get them.

23:20.316 --> 23:21.647
(ROCKS CLATTERING)

23:24.988 --> 23:27.320
All right.
All right.

23:28.825 --> 23:32.363
If we double back,
we should be able to make it
to the village in an hour.

23:35.331 --> 23:37.617
You're not even
going to admit
you were wrong?

23:37.709 --> 23:40.325
You really want to
get into this now?
Come on.

23:40.420 --> 23:42.832
You gotta stop treating me
like your idiot kid brother.

23:42.922 --> 23:45.584
You read the map right.
Congratulations.

23:45.675 --> 23:47.006
God, | wish I could fly.

23:47.093 --> 23:48.299
But you can't.

23:48.386 --> 23:50.001
That's right,
I'm powerless just like you.

23:50.096 --> 23:52.428
Hey, if it wasn't for me,
you'd be lost and alone.

23:52.515 --> 23:54.756
If it wasn't for you,
I'd be home by now.

23:54.851 --> 23:57.513
I only brought you down here
to protect your fragile ego.

23:57.604 --> 23:59.094
You know what?
I don't need your pity.

23:59.188 --> 24:01.770
No, but you know
what you do need?
My help.

24:01.858 --> 24:03.814
I've been saving
your ass my entire life.

24:03.901 --> 24:04.981
Is that so?
That's right.

24:05.069 --> 24:08.653
When you jumped off
that roof like a moron,
who caught you?

24:08.740 --> 24:11.823
Who pulled you out of
Kirby Plaza when you
were about to blow up?

24:11.909 --> 24:14.446
You want my respect?
You want my approval?
Earn it.

24:14.537 --> 24:17.028
Why would I
want your respect?
You're a puppet.

24:19.292 --> 24:20.281
Excuse me?

24:20.376 --> 24:21.957
You have no spine.

24:23.379 --> 24:24.494
I'm a US senator.

24:24.589 --> 24:25.874
No.
You're a nurse.

24:25.965 --> 24:27.956
You're everything
that Dad ever
wanted you to be.

24:28.051 --> 24:30.463
His dreams.
His goals.

24:30.553 --> 24:33.090
He would always find
a way to get under
your skin and manipulate you,

24:33.222 --> 24:34.632
use you.

24:36.059 --> 24:37.549
Where's this coming from?

24:41.481 --> 24:43.517
In the future,
you choose him.

24:44.901 --> 24:46.516
You choose Dad,
Nathan.

24:48.071 --> 24:51.905
I'm down here right now, Pete,
and I'm trying to stop him.

24:53.159 --> 24:54.740
You wanna help me?

25:00.667 --> 25:04.660
Good! Control first,
follow-through second.
You feel that power?

25:04.754 --> 25:06.085
Again.

25:07.423 --> 25:08.412
(EXHALES)

25:09.926 --> 25:11.541
Tell me
what you're thinking.

25:12.345 --> 25:13.585
No.

25:16.516 --> 25:17.756
Tap into that anger.

25:17.850 --> 25:21.013
It will give you strength.
Here, take a swing at me now.

25:21.104 --> 25:22.184
(PANTING)

25:22.271 --> 25:23.681
I don't want to
swing at you.

25:23.773 --> 25:26.059
Come on. Swing at me.

25:26.150 --> 25:28.607
See if you can hit me.
Let's go.

25:33.241 --> 25:34.526
Come on.

25:35.284 --> 25:36.444
(GRUNTING)

25:36.536 --> 25:39.699
You're not even trying,
Claire. Tell me
what you're thinking.

25:41.624 --> 25:44.240
Every time you would
come home from a trip,

25:44.335 --> 25:46.417
I'd always hug you
as tight as I could.

25:46.504 --> 25:47.493
(GRUNTS)

25:48.464 --> 25:51.956
'Cause I thought
if I held you tight enough,
you wouldn't leave me again.

25:54.053 --> 25:56.544
(GROANING)
Why did you
always leave?

25:56.639 --> 25:58.140
(PANTING)

26:02.478 --> 26:04.184
I need to get some air.

26:04.313 --> 26:06.929
Claire, wait a minute,
let's talk about this.

26:07.024 --> 26:09.686
No, I didn't mean
to bring it up.
Just forget it.

26:13.239 --> 26:14.900
Hey, girls.

26:17.910 --> 26:19.161
You have
the Haitian in here?

26:19.245 --> 26:22.157
No. Just me.

26:22.248 --> 26:25.957
Back out of the house now.
You're not getting Claire.

26:26.669 --> 26:28.034
Funny story.

26:28.838 --> 26:30.248
We are.

26:32.759 --> 26:34.169
Claire, stay back.

26:34.260 --> 26:35.249
(CLAIRE GRUNTS)

26:35.344 --> 26:36.720
(BOTH GRUNTING)

26:44.187 --> 26:45.267
(BONE CRACKING)

26:45.354 --> 26:46.343
(SCREAMING)

26:58.201 --> 26:59.361
CLAIRE: No!

26:59.869 --> 27:01.109
Claire!

27:02.705 --> 27:03.694
(GROANS)

27:51.963 --> 27:53.328
Sandra!

27:53.422 --> 27:54.798
(CLAIRE GROANING)

27:55.341 --> 27:57.753
Oh, my God!
What happened?

27:58.094 --> 27:59.129
She got shot.

27:59.220 --> 28:01.381
Okay.
Why isn't she healing?
I don't know.

28:01.472 --> 28:03.428
Something's wrong.
Her ability's not working.

28:03.516 --> 28:05.381
We have to
get her to a hospital.
No.

28:05.476 --> 28:07.637
They report gunshot
wounds to the police.

28:07.728 --> 28:09.980
They'll ask questions.
She is bleeding.

28:10.064 --> 28:11.975
She is hurt.
I'm calling 911.

28:12.066 --> 28:14.148
And what happens
when her healing
comes back?

28:14.235 --> 28:15.725
Noah.
This is a surface wound.

28:15.820 --> 28:18.482
We can deal with it.
Hang up the phone. Please.

28:22.827 --> 28:25.113
I'll get the first-aid kit.
Thank you.

28:25.496 --> 28:27.111
(GROANING IN AGONY)

28:28.499 --> 28:30.535
What happened?
I don't know.

28:30.626 --> 28:31.786
I wish I did.

28:33.754 --> 28:37.747
Maybe you were right.
I have been stupid.
Careless.

28:37.842 --> 28:39.457
I thought
I was invulnerable.

28:41.554 --> 28:43.135
Well, you shouldn't have...

28:45.016 --> 28:48.759
It hurts.
I never thought I'd be
able to hurt again.

28:50.354 --> 28:52.606
It sucks,
but it's wonderful.

28:55.359 --> 28:57.475
Thank you
for saving my life.

28:58.738 --> 28:59.978
Any time.

29:04.994 --> 29:06.609
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:06.913 --> 29:07.948
Still no powers.

29:08.039 --> 29:09.870
Yeah. That much I get.

29:09.957 --> 29:11.618
Why is this happening?
How do we get it back?

29:11.709 --> 29:14.041
Maybe Daphne was right.
Maybe Arthur took them away.

29:14.128 --> 29:16.835
You know, I never,
ever thought that
I would miss my...

29:17.214 --> 29:20.672
Right now, all I wanna do
is just know what's
going on inside her head.

29:20.760 --> 29:21.875
What are we supposed
to do?

29:21.969 --> 29:23.175
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:23.471 --> 29:26.508
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:27.934 --> 29:29.470
He says
you must save Daphne.

29:29.560 --> 29:34.725
(CHUCKLES) I can't. I can't.
Not without my brain thingy.

29:34.815 --> 29:36.191
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:37.234 --> 29:38.269
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:40.446 --> 29:41.811
What?

29:43.991 --> 29:45.026
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:45.117 --> 29:46.778
He says, this is
part of the Hero's Quest.

29:46.869 --> 29:48.234
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:48.329 --> 29:50.285
(TRANSLATING IN ENGLISH)

29:50.581 --> 29:53.323
Hey! Hey!
Seriously,
dude, stop it.

29:53.626 --> 29:54.957
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:55.044 --> 29:56.124
Hey!
Hiro!

29:56.212 --> 29:57.702
How do you say
"stop it"?

29:58.547 --> 29:59.753
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:59.840 --> 30:00.966
(TRANSLATING IN ENGLISH)

30:01.050 --> 30:02.210
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:02.301 --> 30:03.757
(TRANSLATING IN ENGLISH)

30:04.387 --> 30:05.422
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:05.513 --> 30:06.502
(TRANSLATING IN ENGLISH)

30:07.807 --> 30:08.887
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:08.975 --> 30:10.181
You must not doubt.

30:11.435 --> 30:12.845
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:16.565 --> 30:18.647
I'm not gonna hurt you.

30:18.734 --> 30:20.144
I'm gonna save Daphne.

30:22.822 --> 30:24.562
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:25.616 --> 30:27.026
Holy crap.

30:29.620 --> 30:31.485
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:34.375 --> 30:35.455
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:35.584 --> 30:36.664
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:38.629 --> 30:44.966
(BOTH SPEAKING JAPANESE)

31:09.952 --> 31:11.408
It's a miracle.

31:12.163 --> 31:15.246
Complete remission.
All effects of the formula
have disappeared.

31:15.332 --> 31:19.666
Scales. Abilities.
l have no idea how or why.

31:20.463 --> 31:25.002
Some correlation
to the eclipse.
Further study is warranted.

31:28.345 --> 31:29.801
But not yet.

31:40.733 --> 31:45.022
You're not going anywhere.
Now we know the meaning
of the eclipse.

31:45.112 --> 31:47.148
Everyone's abilities
have gone away.

31:48.032 --> 31:49.613
You have to get them back.

31:50.284 --> 31:52.240
I'm not sure that's
entirely possible.

31:52.328 --> 31:54.239
I mean, who knows
what the implications
of this event are?

31:54.330 --> 31:56.070
They could be irreversible.

31:56.165 --> 31:57.951
That's unacceptable.

31:59.502 --> 32:01.208
What are you doing?

32:01.295 --> 32:03.411
Without abilities,
l'm nobody.

32:03.506 --> 32:06.339
I already been nobody.
You understand?

32:06.425 --> 32:12.011
So we're gonna stay
right here until you
get it all back for us.

32:12.098 --> 32:13.087
(GRUNTS)

32:17.061 --> 32:18.926
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

32:23.651 --> 32:25.391
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

32:25.486 --> 32:26.566
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

32:26.654 --> 32:28.519
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

32:39.708 --> 32:41.323
Excuse me.
Yeah, I'll be
with you in a second.

32:41.418 --> 32:44.080
Don't worry.
We got plenty of Red Hu/ks
for everybody.

32:44.839 --> 32:46.454
Sam.
Yeah?

32:52.346 --> 32:54.803
Dude, this is
so awesome.

32:56.559 --> 32:58.641
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

33:06.527 --> 33:07.733
Is he always this quiet?

33:07.820 --> 33:10.357
I don't know.
Why don't you ask him?

33:10.447 --> 33:13.234
Listen, I really appreciate
your help, but we need
to get you back home.

33:15.035 --> 33:16.241
Arthur's alive?

33:16.871 --> 33:19.203
Yeah. You're one
of the only people
who can stop him.

33:19.290 --> 33:21.576
Now, the sooner
you take this
juju off of me,

33:21.667 --> 33:23.828
the sooner
I can fly us home
and deal with him.

33:23.919 --> 33:28.458
I'm not responsible
for your condition.
My ability is gone as well.

33:28.549 --> 33:30.665
The universe has
decided our fate.

33:36.015 --> 33:38.222
Can the universe
get me a phone?

33:38.309 --> 33:41.551
I can call the military.
Get us on a C-130.
Get this sorted.

33:41.645 --> 33:43.806
I'm not going anywhere
until I stop Samedi.

33:43.898 --> 33:45.434
Big guy from Level 5.

33:46.817 --> 33:50.025
l'm responsible
for his evil.
He's my brother.

33:51.030 --> 33:54.864
He's like us. Special.
His skin is impenetrable.

33:55.576 --> 33:58.568
Not by knife.
Not by fire.
Not by bullet.

33:59.330 --> 34:03.699
Many people here
believe him to be a god.
He uses fear to form an army.

34:03.792 --> 34:06.499
They murdered.
Stole. Kidnapped.

34:06.587 --> 34:10.205
I stopped him once,
put him away, but now...

34:12.092 --> 34:13.548
You can't do this
on your own.

34:13.636 --> 34:15.592
Peter, this is
not your fight.

34:15.679 --> 34:18.386
Come on, you helped
our family out once. At least
let us repay that favor.

34:18.474 --> 34:21.841
Hey, look. All right,
you've proved you
can be brave, okay?

34:21.936 --> 34:23.301
Don't be stupid.
(WHISPERING)
Think about it, Nate.

34:23.395 --> 34:25.056
The only way to get
this guy to come back
home with us

34:25.147 --> 34:27.604
is if we help him
stop his brother.

34:27.691 --> 34:29.306
Look, if you're
not gonna do this
for the right reasons,

34:29.401 --> 34:30.937
at least do it
for the selfish ones.

34:31.028 --> 34:32.234
(GUNFIRE)

34:32.321 --> 34:33.356
Samedi! Run!

34:33.447 --> 34:35.153
Move out!
Run! Run!

34:49.380 --> 34:52.793
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

34:58.514 --> 35:02.177
We know all about you,
Senator Nathan Petrelli.

35:02.268 --> 35:04.099
Your father
warned us
you'd come.

35:05.688 --> 35:06.677
My father?

35:06.772 --> 35:07.978
Yes.

35:09.566 --> 35:10.897
What did he tell you?

35:12.945 --> 35:14.685
He told me to be myself.

35:16.699 --> 35:17.814
(SPEAKING CREOLE)

35:44.852 --> 35:46.183
(EXHALING)

35:49.064 --> 35:50.395
No fever.

35:53.402 --> 35:55.313
Are you feeling okay?

35:55.404 --> 35:58.896
Yeah. Pretty good,
all things considered.

36:00.909 --> 36:03.286
We're gonna figure out
what's happening to you.

36:04.246 --> 36:07.909
But for now, you just rest.
I'll be right downstairs.

36:09.752 --> 36:11.413
I love you, Dad.

36:15.424 --> 36:17.130
And I love you,
Claire-bear.

36:33.734 --> 36:35.099
No.

36:35.986 --> 36:37.317
(DOOR CLOSING)

36:38.030 --> 36:39.270
No what?

36:40.157 --> 36:41.897
You're leaving,
aren't you?

36:45.621 --> 36:48.033
Do not leave
your daughter.
Not now.

36:48.123 --> 36:49.203
She's fine.

36:49.291 --> 36:50.792
She's scared.

36:51.502 --> 36:54.835
She doesn't know
what's happening.
She needs you.

36:58.425 --> 37:00.461
There's something
I need to finish.

37:33.210 --> 37:34.495
Daphne?

37:35.504 --> 37:38.120
Daphne, I'm not leaving
until I talk to you.

37:38.215 --> 37:39.671
DAPHNE: GO away, Matt.

37:41.510 --> 37:42.716
No.

37:43.720 --> 37:46.553
No. I came here
because I know
exactly who you are.

37:47.808 --> 37:52.017
You are smart
and beautiful
and funny.

37:52.729 --> 37:57.268
I don't even care
if the spirit walk is all
a bunk. I'm not gonna...

37:57.359 --> 37:59.224
I'm never gonna
give up because...

38:01.238 --> 38:02.899
Because I'm in love
with you.

38:05.576 --> 38:07.032
Daphne!

38:07.953 --> 38:09.363
The door is open.

38:17.212 --> 38:18.292
Daph?

38:18.964 --> 38:20.374
I'm in here.

38:30.976 --> 38:33.342
| just didn't want you
to see me like this.

38:34.062 --> 38:35.313
Like what?

38:45.949 --> 38:47.200
Like this.

38:55.167 --> 38:56.953
How you doing,
sweetie?

